%spark
import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._

val structTypeDDL = "`country` STRING,`description` STRING,`designation` STRING,`points`STRING,`price` BIGINT,`province` STRING,`region_1` STRING,`region_2` STRING,`taster_name` STRING,`taster_twitter_handle` STRING,`title` STRING,`variety` STRING,`winery` STRING"
val wineReviewSchema = StructType.fromDDL(structTypeDDL)

val wineReviews = spark.read.option("inferSchema", "false").schema(wineReviewSchema).json("/svccdata/winereviews.json")
wineReviews.persist()
wineReviews.createOrReplaceTempView("reviews")

paragraphs.title: Price and Variety by Country Stats
paragraphs.text:
%spark
val priceStatsByCountry = wineReviews
  .where(col("country").isNotNull)
  .groupBy("country")
  .agg(
      count("*") as "total",
      min("price") as "min_price",
      avg("price") as "avg_price",
      max("price") as "max_price"
  )

priceStatsByCountry.createOrReplaceTempView("pricebycountry")

/* Price Stats by country / variety */
val priceStatsByCountryAndVariety = wineReviews
  .where(col("variety").isNotNull.and(col("country").isNotNull))
  .groupBy("country", "variety")
  .agg(
      count("*") as "total",
      min("price") as "min_price",
      avg("price") as "avg_price",
      max("price") as "max_price"
  )

priceStatsByCountryAndVariety.createOrReplaceTempView("pricebycountryvariety")

  .withColumn("num_price", 'price.cast("Double"))

paragraphs.title: Look at the Percentiles for top 10 countries by count. Check Distributions
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select country, count(*) as total, min(price) as min, percentile_approx(price, 0.25) as p25, percentile_approx(price, 0.5) as p50, percentile_approx(price, 0.75) as p75, percentile_approx(price, 0.90) as p90, percentile_approx(price, 0.99) as p99, max(price) as max, avg(price) as avg, stddev_pop(price) as stddev
from reviews group by country
order by total DESC
limit 10
